# Online Retail Sales Forecasting and Analysis Report

 1 Introduction

The Online Retail Sales Forecasting project focuses on analyzing transactional retail data and developing machine learning models capable of predicting future revenue trends. The project combines data preprocessing, exploratory data analysis (EDA), feature engineering, predictive modeling, and forecasting techniques to gain insights into customer purchasing behavior and business performance.

Retail businesses generate large amounts of transactional data every day. Extracting meaningful insights from this data helps organizations improve inventory management, customer targeting, sales planning, and revenue forecasting. This project aims to leverage historical sales data to build accurate forecasting models that can estimate future revenue patterns and support data-driven decision making.

The notebook implementation follows a complete machine learning workflow beginning with data loading and cleaning, followed by exploratory analysis, model training, evaluation, and future forecasting. Multiple machine learning algorithms were compared to determine the most suitable model for predicting online retail revenue.


 2 Dataset Description

The dataset used in this project is the “Online Retail” dataset from provided documents, which contains transactional information for an online retail store. The dataset was imported using the Pandas library through the `read_excel()` function.
