14 Performance Evaluation

The performance comparison section evaluated all machine learning models using MAE, RMSE, R² Score, and MAPE.

## Ridge Regression Performance

Ridge Regression provided baseline forecasting performance. It performed adequately for capturing general trends but struggled with nonlinear variations and sudden sales spikes.

### Observations

* Lower complexity
* Faster training time
* Moderate predictive performance

## Random Forest Performance

Random Forest improved forecasting accuracy by learning nonlinear relationships between features and revenue.

### Observations

* Better handling of fluctuations
* Improved robustness
* Reduced prediction errors compared to linear models

##  Gradient Boosting Performance

Gradient Boosting achieved the strongest performance among the tested models.



15 Conclusion

This project successfully demonstrated the application of machine learning techniques for online retail sales analysis and forecasting.

The workflow included:

* Data preprocessing and cleaning
* Exploratory data analysis
